msgid "Use camera for motion detection"
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6688
msgid "Explain camera motion detection"
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6689
msgid ""
"Disables the outside PIR sensor and uses the camera for motion detection "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6690
msgid "**How it works:**"
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6691
msgid ""
"- In regular operation, Kittyhack waits for a trigger from the outside PIR "
"sensor before starting camera analysis"
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6692
msgid ""
"- With this feature enabled, the PIR sensor is disabled and the camera "
"continuously analyzes images"
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6693
msgid ""
"- When a cat is detected in the camera feed, it's treated as equivalent to a "
"motion detection outside"
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6695
msgid ""
"This may be very helpful in areas where environmental factors (moving trees, "
"people passing by) permanently cause false PIR triggers."
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6698
msgid ""
"If one or both are not good, you may experience false triggers or your cat "
"may not be detected correctly."
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6705
msgid "Open inside direction for:"
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6718
msgid "Explain entrance modes"
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6719
msgid ""
"- **All cats:** *Every* detected motion on the outside will unlock the flap."
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6720
msgid ""
"- **All cats with a RFID chip:** Every successful RFID detection will unlock "
"the flap."
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6721
msgid ""
"- **Only registered cats:** Only the cats that are registered in the "
"database will unlock the flap (either by RFID or by camera detection, if "
"enabled)."
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6722
msgid ""
"- **Individual configuration per cat:** Configure per cat if it is allowed "
"to enter (in the `MANAGE CATS` section)."
msgstr ""

#: src/server.py:6723
msgid "- **No cats:** The inside direction will never be opened."
msgstr ""

